Refactor this Python function to remove the nested loops and use a dict for O(1) lookup. Return only the rewritten function.

def find_pairs(items, target):
    out = []
    for i in range(len(items)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(items)):
            if items[i] + items[j] == target:
                out.append((i, j))
    return out

